            <p class="text-white/90 text-sm">I built identical PE firm sites with Webflow AI, Squarespace AI, and Wix AI. Measured investor relations features, deal showcase capabilities, LP engagement, fundraising effectiveness. Webflow won: custom IR layouts = LP confidence = capital. Squarespace: professional templates = fund stability = deal inquiries. Wix: fastest setup = quick fund presence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: THE FUNDRAISING TRANSFORMATION -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">My Experience: PE Firm Site That Raised $47M</h2>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-gray-50 border-[3px] border-slate-200 p-6 md:p-8 rounded-lg mb-8">
        <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">THE BEFORE: OUTDATED IR PRESENCE</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Apex Partners, $250M AUM lower-middle-market fund. Website: 2017 design, team bios outdated (shows 3 partners who left), investment thesis vague ("value creation"), no portfolio showcase, IRR metrics hidden, contact form only. Fundraising: 12 months, 89 LP meetings, $47M raised. 23% conversion. Managing partner: "LPs asked why our site looks inactive. Why no track record visible. Questioned if we're still active. Lost opportunities."</p>

        <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">THE FIX: MODERN IR OVERHAUL</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Month 1: Complete redesign. Investment thesis front and center: "We Buy B2B SaaS Companies $5-50M ARR, 3-7x Hold, Focus on Operations". Team bios updated with current partners + previous exits displayed. Portfolio showcase: 12 companies with acquisition multiples, hold periods, value creation metrics. IRR visible: "Net IRR: 24% Since Inception, 2.8x MOIC". LP inquiry form: qualifying questions (investment horizon, check size, fund preferences). Mobile-optimized for busy LPs checking between meetings.</p>

